# Documentation Authority

Canonical precedence for every agent and maintainer. When two documents
disagree, the higher tier wins. Lower tiers must be updated to match or
explicitly marked `historical` / `derived`.

## Tier Ladder

```text
Tier 0 — Runtime proof
  code, tests, package scripts, project oracles

Tier 1 — Product truth
  README.md, docs/roadmap.md, docs/decisions/**

Tier 2 — Agent operating line
  EXECUTION-LINE, PROJECT-STATE, PROJECT-ROADMAP, QUALITY-GATES,
  BOUNDARIES-AND-CONSTRAINTS, GLOSSARY, this file

Tier 3 — Derived contracts and init inventory
  docs/agents/contracts/** (mirror Tier 1+2; never lead)
  PROJECT-CONTEXT.md (init inventory after /tes-init; subordinate after /tes-align)
  PROJECT-REGISTER.md (deterministic inventory)

Tier 4 — Archive and evidence
  docs/agents/evidence/**, retired methodology trees, historical snapshots
  (proof and audit only — not current-state authority)
```

## Reading Order (cold start)

1. This file — tier ladder and precedence.
2. [[EXECUTION-LINE]] — current lane and stop conditions.
3. [[PROJECT-STATE]] — done / active / blocked / unknown.
4. Product roadmap and relevant `docs/decisions/**`.
5. [[QUALITY-GATES]] + [[BOUNDARIES-AND-CONSTRAINTS]] before editing.
6. Source code and tests to falsify claims.

Do **not** start from `PROJECT-CONTEXT.md` or Tier 4 archives for current position.

## Phase Vocabulary Bridge

When Tier 1 and Tier 2 use different done/active vocabulary (for example a
shipped MVP scope vs a formal phase closure in the product roadmap), record the
bridge in an ADR under `docs/agents/DECISIONS/**` and in alignment evidence.
Do not collapse both claims into one lane without explicit scoping.

## Inventory Hygiene

Every `/tes-align` must scrub Tier 3 inventory when
`docs/agents/contracts/INVENTORY-HYGIENE.yml` exists:

- Remove Tier 4 paths from **Recommended Deep Reads** in `PROJECT-CONTEXT.md`.
- Point deep reads to [[DOCUMENTATION-AUTHORITY]] and [[EXECUTION-LINE]] first.
- Refresh Git HEAD in the Identity table (see skill note on commit timing).
- Keep `tier: 3-inventory` in frontmatter.

Run `python3 scripts/verify_documentation_inventory.py --target .` before PASS.

## Locks

- Tier 3 contracts and init inventory never override Tier 2 position.
- Tier 4 is evidence and history, not operating authority.
- Retired terms belong in `docs/agents/contracts/SEMANTIC-RESIDUE.yml`, not skill bodies.
